
# Project Setup

> **First time?** Follow [ONBOARDING.md](ONBOARDING.md) to install all prerequisites.
> **Just want to run it?** See [QUICKSTART.md](QUICKSTART.md).

## Prerequisites

- Python {{ python_version }}+ (managed via UV)
- Bun (frontend runtime & package manager)
- [Task](https://taskfile.dev) (task runner)
- {{ container_runtime | title }} (container engine)
- VS Code (recommended — open `{{ project_slug }}.code-workspace`)

## Initial Setup

```bash
task setup     # Installs deps, pre-commit hooks, creates .env
task docker:up # Start all container services
task test      # Verify everything works
```


Open the **multi-root workspace** for pre-configured settings, launch
configs, and extension recommendations:

```
{{ project_slug }}.code-workspace
```

When prompted, install the recommended extensions. Full details,
optional extensions, keybindings, and user settings are in
`docs/VSCODE.md`.


```bash
cd backend
uv sync --all-groups
uv run pytest
```


```bash
cd frontend
bun install
bun dev
```


Copy `.env.example` to `.env` and configure:

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

Replace all `__CHANGE_ME__` placeholders with generated secrets before sharing environments.

For shared deployments, copy `.env.example` to the appropriate env file
(`.env.dev`, `.env.test`, `.env.staging`, `.env.prod`) and adjust the values
listed in the "Per-Environment Quick Reference" section at the bottom of the file.

For local-only personal overrides:

- backend/global overrides: `.env.local` (start from `.env.local.example`)
- frontend overrides: `frontend/.env.local` (start from `frontend/.env.local.example`)

Key variables are documented in `docs/CONFIG.md`.
