## Knowledge Graph Setup
{% if knowledge_graph_backend == 'neo4j' %}

### Neo4j

The project uses Neo4j 5 as its knowledge graph backend. Start Neo4j
through the Compose `knowledge-graph` profile:

```bash
{{ container_runtime }} compose --profile knowledge-graph up -d neo4j
```

Neo4j exposes:

| Service | URL |
|---------|-----|
| Browser UI | `http://localhost:7474` |
| Bolt protocol | `bolt://localhost:7687` |

Default credentials are `neo4j` / `changeme` (set `NEO4J_AUTH` in
`compose.yml` or `.env` to change).

Configure the backend connection in `.env`:

```
{{ project_slug | upper }}_KNOWLEDGE_GRAPH_BACKEND=neo4j
{{ project_slug | upper }}_NEO4J_URI=bolt://localhost:7687
{{ project_slug | upper }}_NEO4J_USER=neo4j
{{ project_slug | upper }}_NEO4J_PASSWORD=changeme
{{ project_slug | upper }}_NEO4J_DATABASE=neo4j
```

Install Neo4j system-wide (optional — the Compose service is
sufficient for development):

```bash
zsh scripts/install/install-neo4j.zsh
```
{% elif knowledge_graph_backend == 'rdflib' %}

### RDFLib

The project uses RDFLib as its knowledge graph backend. No external
services are required — the graph runs in-process. Configure persistence
in `.env`:

```
{{ project_slug | upper }}_KNOWLEDGE_GRAPH_BACKEND=rdflib
{{ project_slug | upper }}_KNOWLEDGE_GRAPH_PATH=data/kg/graph.ttl
```
{% else %}

### NetworkX (default)

The project uses NetworkX as its knowledge graph backend. No external
services are required — the graph runs in-process. Configure persistence
in `.env`:

```
{{ project_slug | upper }}_KNOWLEDGE_GRAPH_BACKEND=networkx
{{ project_slug | upper }}_KNOWLEDGE_GRAPH_PATH=data/kg/graph.json
```
{% endif %}

See `docs/CONFIG.md` for the full list of knowledge graph environment
variables.
