## Workflow Checkpointers

LangGraph workflows use checkpointers for durable execution and
state persistence. Three backends are supported:

| Backend | Use case | Persistence | Config |
|---------|----------|-------------|--------|
| Memory | Development, tests | None (in-process) | Default |
| SQLite | Local dev, staging | File-based (`.langgraph_checkpoints.db`) | `{{ project_slug | upper }}_CHECKPOINTER_BACKEND=sqlite` |
| PostgreSQL | Production | Database-backed | `{{ project_slug | upper }}_CHECKPOINTER_BACKEND=postgres` |

SQLite requires no external services. The checkpoint database file is
created automatically in the project root on first workflow execution.

To inspect the SQLite checkpoint database:

```bash
sqlite3 .langgraph_checkpoints.db ".tables"
```

To reset checkpoint state:

```bash
rm -f .langgraph_checkpoints.db
```

For production, use the PostgreSQL checkpointer. It reuses the
application database connection configured via `{{ project_slug | upper }}_DATABASE_URL`.

> SQLite uses WAL mode for better concurrent read performance. Avoid
> running multiple writer processes against the same SQLite checkpoint
> file.
